# .NET Backend Defaults (overridable by project)

If the repo has `AGENTS.md`, `.cursorrules`, or `.cursor/rules/*` with stricter/project-specific rules — **those win**.

Otherwise, prefer:

## Architecture

- Clean Architecture: Api → Application → Domain; Infrastructure implements Application ports
- CQRS with MediatR (Command/Query + Handler) when the project already uses it
- Prefer Result / Result\<T\> over throwing for expected business failures
- Always check `IsSuccess` (or equivalent) before accessing `.Value`

## API

- Match existing HTTP status conventions of the project
- If project uses Carter/minimal APIs: keep that style; never invent MVC controllers into a Carter codebase
- Auth + rate limiting on endpoints when the project already does so

## Data

- Soft delete when `IsDeleted` / global filters exist — never hard `Remove()` unless project does hard deletes
- Do not hand-edit EF `Migrations/**` — flag migration commands for the human
- Forward `CancellationToken` on all async I/O
- Read queries: `.AsNoTracking()` when not mutating

## Mapping / DI

- Prefer the project's existing mapper (Mapster / AutoMapper / manual) — do not introduce a second mapper
- Prefer primary constructors for handlers/services when the codebase uses them

## Discovery

Before scaffolding: search for existing Endpoint/Handler/DTO/entity via codebase-memory MCP.
